70s, when existentialism was all the rage and everyone was carrying around tattered copies of

03:59.440 --> 04:10.480
Camus and Sartre and Beauvoir. And and my parents met in graduate school. And so I was surrounded

04:10.480 --> 04:20.240
by books growing up. And I in my second semester of college, I was actually an engineering major

04:20.240 --> 04:26.880
in college, believe it or not. And the second semester of college, I read Dostoevsky's The

04:26.880 --> 04:35.680
Brothers Karamazov during the winter break. And the book had a transformative impact on me.

04:36.560 --> 04:43.360
